    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect SDAP header construction in TUN read thread\n\n### Summary\nThe `sdap_tun_read_thread` function in the NR SDAP layer was constructing SDAP headers with incorrect DC/RQI bit values, causing data packets to be misinterpreted by the receiving entity. This issue manifested as dropped user plane packets and connectivity problems in NSA mode when traffic was flowing through the TUN interface.\n\nThe root cause was that the `rqi` parameter (which becomes the DC bit for UL or RQI bit for DL) was being set based on whether the entity was gNB or UE, rather than using the appropriate constant values for data PDUs.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/SDAP/nr_sdap/nr_sdap.c`: \n  - Fixed incorrect logic for setting the `rqi` parameter in `sdap_tun_read_thread`\n  - Replaced hardcoded DRB ID (1) with entity's default DRB\n  - Added safety check for valid default DRB configuration\n  - Improved code comments for clarity\n\n"
}